{"accepted":[{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Full solution.","id":"vf_04cbe2552ae8d328","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #690: declared status 'solved'. Formalized: no. Let $d_k(p)$ be the density of those integers whose $k$th smallest prime factor is $p$ (i.e. if $p_1<p_2<\\cdots$ are the primes dividing $n$ then $p_k=p$).\n\nFor fixed $k\\geq 1$ is $d_k(p)$ unimodular in $p$? That is, it first increases in $p$ until its maximum then decreases. Current best: Cambie \\cite{Ca25} has shown that $d_k(p)$ is unimodular for $1\\leq k\\leq 3$ and is not unimodular for $4\\leq k\\leq 20$. Prize: no. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_1ef7e98a41ecd48c","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/690.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_04cbe2552ae8d328","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:690","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_1ef7e98a41ecd48c","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:690","trust":"signed"}],"external_references":[],"formal_conjectures_activity":null,"frontier_id":"vfr_0a25edabc16db143","frontier_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","label":"Erdős 690","lenses":{"all_authored":false,"current_record":false,"mathematical_work":false,"research_plus_scouting":false},"lifecycle":"unstarted","location":"reference_only","machine_status":"not_checked","mathematical_scope":"not_applicable","method_channels":[],"nodes":[{"id":"er